        "timestamp": "2018-05-29 15:16:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nSonar does not handle the concept of branches properly. \nCreating a beijing branch for Sonar will cause the job to overlap test\nscan results. \n\nThe proper way of using Sonar is to have it running on the master,\nresolve any issues in master and propagate those fixes into the \nrelease branches.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
